<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Plans to Build Network of Coastal Expressways </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 4 (Xinhua) -- India is planning to build a
massive network of coastal expressways linking all major ports in
the country and the national capital, a cabinet minister said here
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Union Surface Transport Minister Thambi Durai told a press
conference that his ministry has already submitted a note to the
cabinet for its approval of the plan to facilitate faster movement
of container traffic.
</P>
<P>
Durai said the existing highways are inadequate to take care of
rapidly increasing container traffic in the country, adding that
the proposed expressways would be on the lines of the first-ever
six-lane expressway being constructed between Numbai and Pune in
the western state of Maharashtra.
</P>
<P>
Total cost of the entire project is estimated at 200 billion
rupees (about 5 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
However, Durai did not give any time-frame for the completion
of the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
