<HEADLINE> International Furniture Fair Opens in Bucharest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The seventh edition of the
International Furniture Fair opened at the Romexpo Exhibition
Center here Friday, bringing together as many as 340 firms from 19
countries.
</P>
<P>
The one-week fair, appraised as the fifth in size after
Cologne, Milan, Brussels and Paris, counts 22 pavilions, covering
a floor space of 25,560 square meters. Wood products, paper,
cardboard, packages and forestry exploitation equipment are also
among the exhibits.
</P>
<P>
Firms from Belgium, Great Britain, Pakistan and Sweden are
participating for the first time this year, together with those
from Austria, the Czech Republic, Denmark, Switzerland, Germany,
Italy, the Republic of Moldova, the Netherlands, Poland, the USA,
Slovenia, Spain, Turkey and Hungary.
</P>
<P>
Romania has a long tradition in wood processing and furniture
making. Twenty-eight percent of its territory is covered by
forests. More than 100,000 workers and experts work in this
industry which means 4.76 percent of the total manpower. The
volume of exports was 450 million U.S. dollars in 1997 which is 7
percent of the total Romanian exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
