<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin Proclaims Victory Over Floods (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JIUJIANG, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today declared that the two-month flood control effort has
achieved decisive victory and urged the country to shift its
priorities to reconstruction and attaining this year's growth
target.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, also general secretary of the Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China and chairman of the Central Military
Commission, made the remarks in Jiujiang, Jiangxi Province, the
second stop of his ongoing fact-finding tour which started on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He said soldiers and local residents have battled courageously
and worked tenaciously to hold back raging flood waters over the
past two months.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said they have protected the safety of levees, major
cities along the rivers and main railway lines, and have saved an
untold number of lives. "We have successfully waged a 'People's
War' in advance of the new century," said the president.
</P>
<P>
The monumental success will have far-reaching significance in
terms of helping maintain social stability required by reform,
opening-up and modernization construction.
</P>
<P>
"The effort has once again clearly revealed the cohesiveness
and tenacity of forces of the Communist Party of China, the
superiority of socialism and the reliability of our army," said
Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out continued efforts will be required to achieve
ultimate triumph over the flooding. He said that flood waters are
gradually receding and stressed that disaster regions should shift
their efforts to relief work and reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
Priority should be providing for the basic daily needs of flood
victims, preventing the spread of diseases and maintaining
security in disaster areas, said Jiang, adding that a nationwide
campaign to build and repair water conservation projects must be
organized immediately.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
