<HEADLINE> President Jiang Zemin Proclaims Victory Over Floods (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The president called on the entire nation to assist flood
victims in efforts to resume farming production and construct new
homes. However, he urged people in disaster areas to practice
self-reliance in the reconstruction effort.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed confidence in prospects for fulfilling this
year's economic growth target and noted that disaster relief
efforts and reconstruction will stimulate domestic demand and
promote growth.
</P>
<P>
He said great importance should be attached to building a
comprehensive water conservancy network which will be crucial for
controlling floods in years to come.
</P>
<P>
Jiang visited a number of evacuation centers, temporary
medical stations and makeshift schools.
</P>
<P>
When Jiang arrived at Yueliangwan Street in the West District
of Jiujiang City, a street that had experienced the heaviest flood
waters about a month ago, local people poured out to greet the
president. Jiang talked with them, inquiring about their life and
work.
</P>
<P>
Braving rain and wind, Jiang also visited the Guodongyu Levee
in Yongxiu County, where a People's Liberation Army unit is
stationed to combat the floods and protect the dykes. Jiang
extended warm regards to the soldiers and officers there and
entered some tents to chat with armymen.
</P>
<P>
Some officials from central Party and government departments
accompanied Jiang on the tour. 
</P>
</TEXT>
