<HEADLINE> Russian Service Confirms DPRK Satellite Launch </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A Russian agency has confirmed
that the Democratic People's Republic of Korea successfully
launched its first national artificial earth satellite Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Russian Service for the Monitoring of Space Objects said
the satellite was launched from the Musudan ground, at 40.8
degrees of northern latitude and 129.7 degrees of eastern
longitude, the Itar-Tass reported.
</P>
<P>
According to a representative of the service, the satellite was
put on the orbit with a minimum distance from the Earth surface of
218.82 kilometers, a maximum distance from the Earth surface of
6,978.2 kilometers and a period of rotation of 165 minutes 06
seconds, a high-elliptic orbit.
</P>
<P>
He said the launch of the satellite to an orbit with such
parameters was, presumably, by a powerful rocket-booster, whose
tactic-technical parameters were not inferior to characteristics
of an inter-continental missile, Tass reported. 
