<HEADLINE> China, Angola Ink Economic Housing Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese company, Jiangsu
International Cooperation Company, signed a housing contract
worth 11 million U.S. Dollars with Angola here Friday.
</P>
<P>
This community housing is the first Chinese-assisted project
in Angola and it will be well furnished and equipped.
</P>
<P>
According to the contract, 195 apartments (72 two-rooms and
123 three-rooms) covering a total floor space of 15,197 square
meters will be built in 18 months.
</P>
<P>
After the signing ceremony, Caetalu Francisco Baiao, director
in charge of legal affairs in the secretariat of the Angolan
housing ministry, said that the project is suitable for Angola.
</P>
<P>
Baiao added that the signing of the housing contract has
special significance before Angolan President Jose Eduardo dos
Santos visits China, and will surely contribute to the
cooperation between the two countries in other fields.
</P>
<P>
The vice-president of the Chinese company, Guo Huadong, signed
the contract with some Chinese diplomats in presence. 
</P>
