<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Earmarks $138M for Road Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian Roads
Authority announced Friday that it has earmarked over one billion
Birr (138 million U.S. Dollars) for the construction of roads,
bridges and maintenance centers in current 1998/99 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The authority has plans to execute the construction of 373
kilometers of road, six bridges and two maintenance centers on
its own at a cost of over 208 million Birr (28.6 million U.S.
Dollars), Tesfa-Michael Nahusenaye, General Manager of the
authority, is quoted by the Ethiopian News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
According to Tesfa-Michael, the road projects include, among
others, the construction of Sodo-West Abaya and the West
Abaya-Arbaminch new asphalt road as well as Gedo-Fincha,
Azezo-Metema and Harar-Jijiga-Degehabour-Shekosh Shilabo Fidder
roads.
</P>
<P>
The general manager said that the construction of Addis
Ababa-Mojo-Awassa, Addis Ababa-Jimma, Addis Ababa-Debre Markos,
Chada-Sodo, Shire-Shiraro-Humera as well as Mile-Chafara-Woldiya
roads will also be undertaken.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian government has plans to increase the country's
road mileage to 30,200 kms including 7,100 kms of asphalt road
after a five-year (1997/98-2001/02) road program.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia had 24,000 kms of road including 3,500 kms of asphalt
road before the program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
