<HEADLINE> Explosion Rocks Daghestani Capital, 4 Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 4 (Xinhua) -- A powerful explosion rocked an
elite district in Makhachkala, capital of Russia's Daghestani
autonomous republic, on Friday, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
Four people were killed and at least 20 others, including
children, were wounded in the blast, which left a crater with a
radius of five meters and a depth of two-three meters.
</P>
<P>
Tass quoted witnesses as saying that the explosion was caused
by a guided missile. There were also reports that the bomb was
planted in a sewage shaft. Neither version was confirmed by the
authorities.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred on Parkhomenko street, in a rich
neighborhood where Chairman of the Daghestani government Khizri
Shikhsayedov and Makhachkala Mayor Sayed Amirov live.
</P>
<P>
However, preliminary reports said neither Shikhsayedov nor
Amirov was hurt.
</P>
<P>
The buildings near the blast site were damaged, some totally
destroyed. Emergency staff are searching the debris for survivors.
</P>
