<HEADLINE> Morocco's El Guerrouj Wins Moscow GP Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 5 (Xinhua) -- World champion Hicham El
Guerrouj kept his winning streak intact and was guaranteed at
least one third of the one-million dollars bonus by winning the
1,500 meters with ease at the IAAF Grand Prix Finals here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Moroccan, who set the world record in July, ran alone for
the final lap, clocking in 3 minutes 32.03 seconds, a full second
better than runner-up Noah Ngeny.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Guerrouj picked up no less than a third of the
one million dollars Golden League jackpot, plus 200,000 dollars
as overall men's Grand Prix champion and 50,000 for winning his
race on the sport's single biggest payday.
</P>
<P>
The other two candidates for the bonus were Marion Jones of
the United States in the women's 100 meters and Haile
Gebrselassie of Ethiopia in the 3,000 meters.
</P>
<P>
The one million dollars jackpot is for athletes who win their
event at all six Golden League meets plus the Grand Prix Final.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the Moscow Grand Prix, the only other person in
contention for the big prize was Byan Bronson, but the American
finished only sixth in the 400 hurdles which was won by France's
world champion Stephane Diagana in 48.30 seconds. 
</P>
