<HEADLINE> Kim Jong Il Elected NDC Chairman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PYONGYANG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Kim Jong Il, general
secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea, was re-elected the
chairman of the National Defense Commission (NDC) on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kim, 56, also the supreme commander of the Korean People's
Army, was re-elected at the first session of the 10th Supreme
People's Assembly (SPA) which began in the Mansudae Assembly Hall
Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
"It was declared at the session that he was elected NDC
chairman by the will and desire of all the people and servicemen
of the country," the Korean Central News Agency said.
</P>
<P>
"He has conducted energetic revolutionary activities for
decades to carry forward the revolutionary cause of the great
leader kim il sung," said the agency.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that his election clearly demonstrated the will
and resolution of all the members of the Worker's Party, other
working people and servicemen of Korea to "smash all the
challenges and anti-DPRK moves of the imperialists and
reactionaries, turn the country into a powerful socialist state
and exalt the dignity and honor of Juche Korea in the 21st
century."
</P>
<P>
Under the DPRK's constitution, the NDC is the highest military
supervisory body of the country.
</P>
<P>
Kim Jong Il was first appointed the NDC chairman for a
five-year term in April 1993 after his father, Kim Il Sung,
vacated the position.
</P>
<P>
At the first session of the 10th SPA, Jo Myong Rok was elected
the NDC's first vice-chairman while Kim Il Chol and Ri Yong Mu
were elected the vice chairmen of the commission.
</P>
<P>
The session also elected six members of the commission -- Kim
Yong Chun, Yon Hyong Muk, Ri Ul Sol, Paek Hak Rim, Jon Pyong Ho,
Kim Chol Man.
</P>
<P>
Choe Thae Bok was elected the SPA chairman of the SPA while
Jang Chol and Ryo Won Gu were elected the vice chairmen of the
assembly. 
</P>
</TEXT>
