<HEADLINE> China Wins Three Titles in Asian Badminton Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese shuttlers won
three out of five titles at the Asian Badminton Championships
which concluded here Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
Ye Zhaoying won the women's title as she outwitted her
compatriot Gong Zhichao 11-5, 13-12 in an all-Chinese affair, and
Ge Fei who paired with Gu Jun won the women's doubles title in
another all-Chinese finals by beating Qing Yiyuan and Tang Hetian
15-8, 15-7.
</P>
<P>
In the men's singles final, Chen Gang awarded China the third
gold medal by outplaying Maleve Mainaky of Indonesia 15-6, 15-9.
</P>
<P>
The men's doubles title was slipped out the hands of a Chinese
pair of Zhang Jun and Zhang Wei.
</P>
<P>
After winning the first set 15-12, the Chinese pair was
outwitted 11-15 by their South Korean peers Kang Kyung Jin and Ha
Tae Kwon.
</P>
<P>
In the decisive third set, the Chinese shuttlers once surged
to a dominant advantage of 12-6 but only to be toppled out of
rhythm as the Korean men scored eights points in a row to
overturn the scoreboard 14-12 en route to their victory of 15-13.
</P>
<P>
In the mixed doubles, Chinese Sun Jun and Ge Fei were beaten
by their Korean counterparts Kim Dong Moon and Ra Kyung Min 15-7,
15-8 in the first of the five finals competed tonight.
</P>
<P>
The Asian Championships was started on September 1 with the
participation of athletes from 24 countries and regions. 
</P>
