<HEADLINE> Taliban Says Iranian Diplomats May Have Been Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia
said Saturday that there was a "strong possibility" that Iranian
diplomats reportedly taken hostage by the Taliban in Afghanistan
had been killed.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here Saturday afternoon from Kabul quoted
Taliban spokesman Wakil Ahmed Mutawakkil as saying, "the
possibility of their being killed is strong."
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the Taliban will come up with an answer on
the fate of the 10 Iranian diplomats and a correspondent of the
Iranian News Agency, known as IRNA.
</P>
<P>
A commission made up of the Taliban militia, Iran and Pakistan
is to investigate the matter under an agreement reached this week.
</P>
<P>
The Iranians remained missing since the Taliban militia stormed
the northern Afghan town of Mazar-i-Sharif, the stronghold of the
anti-Taliban Northern Alliance on August 8. The Iranian consulate
in the city was reported to be raided.
</P>
<P>
Iran insists that the 10 diplomats and one IRNA correspondent
are being held by the Taliban in Kandahar. However, the
allegations have repeatedly been denied by the Taliban.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban spokesman said that "within the next week, we will
try to find the bodies of the dead diplomats." 
</P>
