<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Industrial and Commercial
Bank of China (ICBC) plans to increase its credit line for this
year by 35 billion yuan (about 4.2 billion U.S. dollars) to
support infrastructure construction.
</P>
<P>
The decision came following the recent issuance of an
additional 100 billion yuan in treasury bonds by the Ministry of
Finance, of which ICBC subscribed 50 billion yuan, the most among
all state commercial banks.
</P>
