<HEADLINE> Australia, Belgium Win Triathlon Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Rina Hill of Australia and Luc
Van Lierde of Belgium won the women's and men's titles at the
World Long Distance Triathlon Championships in Sado Island, Japan
on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hill, who won the title for the first time, covered the
distance of 167 kilometers in 6 hours 32 minutes and 09 seconds,
beating Lena Wahlqvist of Sweden to second in 6:37:50.
</P>
<P>
Megumi Shigaki awarded Japan its first medal by finishing
third in 6:40:41.
</P>
<P>
Hill, 29, who won the World Cup in July in Japan, led the 3-km
swimming in 42:29, almost 30 seconds ahead of Wahlqvist while the
136-km bike section was won by Maryke Zeekant of the Netherlands
in 3:51.39, who eventually finished fourth.
</P>
<P>
Hill regained the lead in the 28-km running section by
clocking 1:54:59 for the victory.
</P>
<P>
In the men's race, Van Lierde stormed back from third place in
the swimming section to snatch the lead on the first lap of the
bike section and never looked back afterwards for an easy victory.
</P>
<P>
He timed 38:54, 3:20:01 and 1:44:08 in the three sections. Rob
Barel of the Netherlands came in second in 5:52:32, followed by
Peter Sandvang of Denmark third in 5:52:33. 
</P>
