<HEADLINE> G-7 Officials Invited to London on Russia Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Britain has sent invitations to
the Group of Seven (G-7) nations to a meeting in London next week
to discuss the crisis in Russia, British officials said on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The officials said invitations were sent by British Junior
Foreign Minister Joyce Quin at a meeting of European Union foreign
ministers in Salzburg, Austria. But the exact date for the meeting
has not been decided yet.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials from the Finance Ministry and Foreign Ministry
of the G-7 nations are expected to attend the meeting chaired by
Sir Nigel Wicks, a top British Treasury official.
</P>
<P>
Britain is the current rotational chairman of the G-7 nations
which includes Britain, the United States, France, Germany, Italy,
Japan and Canada.
</P>
<P>
Representatives from the International Monetary Fund, the World
Bank and the European Commission will also attend the meeting,
while Russian officials were not invited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
