<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Congress of Chinese Women Concludes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The six-day Eighth National
Congress of Chinese Women ended here this afternoon after electing
a new leadership for the All-China Women's Federation (ACWF) and
revising the federation's constitution.
</P>
<P>
At the closing meeting of the conference, 1,300 women delegates
from all over the country approved a work report delivered by the
Seventh ACWF Executive Committee, as well as a draft amendment to
the ACWF constitution.
</P>
<P>
The revised constitution added Deng Xiaoping's Theory as a
guiding ideology for the women's movement in China.
</P>
<P>
During the conference, Peng Peiyun, vice-chairwoman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress, China's top
legislature, was elected new president of the ACWF, with Gu
Xiulian and 11 others elected vice-presidents.
</P>
<P>
Chen Muhua, president of the Seventh ACWF Executive Committee,
became honorary president of the ACWF.
</P>
<P>
The conference also elected the ACWF's new executive committee
and standing committee, as well as a new secretariat headed by Gu
Xiulian.
</P>
<P>
The newly elected Peng promised at the closing meeting that the
ACWF will make further efforts to protect women's rights and
interests and promote equality between men and women in China,
which she said are the federation's fundamental functions.
</P>
<P>
She also urged women's federations at all levels to be more
concerned about female workers laid off from state-owned
enterprises and to help create more job opportunities for them.
</P>
<P>
Delegates to the congress -- including those from the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region, Macao and Taiwan -- donated more
than 286,000 yuan (35,000 U.S. dollars) and 88,000 Hong Kong
dollars to the flood victims in the Yangtze, Nenjiang and
Songhuajiang river basins.
</P>
<P>
Founded in 1949, the All-China Women's Federation is a
non-governmental organization of women under the leadership of the
Communist Party of China. The National Congress of Chinese Women,
paramount power organ of the ACWF, is held once every five years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
