<HEADLINE> Japanese Snatches WBA Super Featherweight Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Challenger Takanori Hatakeyama
won the title of the World Boxing Association (WBA) super
featherweight champion, beating eight-time defending champion
Choi Yong-Soo of South Korea in a 2-0 decision Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Two judges counted it both 116-113 in favor of the challenger
with only one judge scoring it 114-114 even.
</P>
<P>
It was a sweet victory for Hatakeyama, who drew with
title-defending Choi at his first attempt at a world title in
October last year.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Japanese, ranked second in the WBA, improved
his record to 22 wins, including 18 KOs, and a draw.
</P>
<P>
Choi, who became the champion in October 1995, saw his record
reduced to 24 wins, including 14 KOs, against three defeats and a
draw. 
</P>
</TEXT>
