<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Strengthens Currency Board System </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA), Hong Kong's de facto central bank, Saturday
announced a package of seven technical measures to strengthen the
currency board system.
</P>
<P>
In its first measure, the HKMA provides a clear undertaking to
all licensed banks in Hong Kong to convert Hong Kong dollars in
their clearing accounts into U.S. dollars at the fixed exchange
rate of 7.75 to one.
</P>
<P>
Joseph Yam, chief executive of the HKMA, said at a press
conference here Saturday: "This explicit convertibility
undertaking is a clear demonstration of the government's
commitment to the linked exchange rate system."
</P>
<P>
He explained that 7.75 was chosen "because it is the current
intervention rate of the HKMA". Under the currency board
arrangements, every 7.8 HK dollars issued is 100 percent backed by
one U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
Before he unveiled the new initiatives, Yam reiterated two
preconditions, saying: "First, the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR) is firmly committed to the maintenance
of the linked exchange rate system and the adherence to the
discipline of the currency board arrangements under the system."
</P>
<P>
"Second, there will be no foreign exchange controls in the
HKSAR," he said.
</P>
<P>
He announced that the HKMA will, starting from September 7,
introduce a discount window arrangement to replace the present
Liquidity Adjustment Facility (LAF), a mechanism introduced in
1992 to facilitate interbank liquidity.
</P>
<P>
The specific measures involved are to lift the restriction on
repeated borrowing of banks for provision of overnight Hong Kong
dollar liquidity, to remove the LAF bid rate, and to shift the LAF
offer rate into the base rate of the discount window.
</P>
<P>
Yam said: "The discount rate will be determined from time to
time by the HKMA, which will ensure that interest rates are
adequately responsive to capital flows, and on the other hand,
ensure that excessive volatility of interest rate is dampened."
</P>
<P>
As from September 7, the HKMA will announce each day before the
market opens in Hong Kong the base rate applicable for the day, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The HKMA will also introduce a schedule of discount rates for
licensed banks that make access to the discount window with the
Exchange Fund paper in hand. In another measure, the HKMA made it
clear that no new issues of paper other than Exchange Fund paper
will be accepted at the discount window.
</P>
<P>
To make sure that all new Exchange Fund paper will be fully
backed by foreign currency reserves, the HKMA committed that new
Exchange Fund paper will only be issued when there is an inflow of
funds.
</P>
<P>
"The package of seven measures is introduced to purify the
currency board arrangements, and make them less susceptible to
manipulation by speculators in the interbank market," said Yam.
</P>
<P>
He added that the HKMA will enhance the transparency of the
currency board operations by disclosing related materials
frequently. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980905.0107 </DOCNO>
