<HEADLINE> HK Forms Information Infrastructure Advisory Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's Information
Technology and Broadcasting Bureau announced Saturday the setting
up of the Information Infrastructure Advisory Committee and the
appointment of committee members by the Chief Executive.
</P>
<P>
The committee will advise the government on the policy,
regulatory, technical and other related issues in the further
development and enhancement of the physical communications
infrastructure in Hong Kong, the development of an open, common
interface through which individuals, business and government can
interact easily and securely use their own systems, and the
development of applications which make effective use of the common
 interface.
</P>
<P>
The committee will also advise the government on the
formulation of Hong Kong's position at, and contribution to,
international and regional fora on issues relating to the global
and regional information infrastructure and electronic commerce,
and the promotion of community awareness and creative use of
information technology.
</P>
<P>
The committee is chaired by Secretary for Information
Technology and Broadcasting Kwong Ki-chi, with members including
leading figures from the information technology and
telecommunications fields, academia, business as well as
representatives from the government.
</P>
<P>
The members will hold its first meeting on September 11.
</P>
</TEXT>
