<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Highest August Mean Temperature Recorded in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 5 (Xinhua) -- August 1998 was surely among
 the hottest Augusts in the memory of Hong Kong people, with the
mean temperature of the month reaching 29.5 degrees Celsius,
leveling the record made in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Observatory said Saturday that under the
continual influence of a ridge of high pressure during most parts
of August, there were long periods of sunshine and the total
rainfall of the month was below normal.
</P>
<P>
The maximum temperatures at the observatory were higher than
33.0 degrees Celsius on four consecutive days in early August,
which is "rather rare in recent years," said the observatory.
</P>
<P>
The mean temperature from January to August this year, at 24.0
degrees Celsius, also hit a record high since the observatory
started weather recording over a century ago. The previous record
was 23.8 degrees Celsius during the same period in 1966 and 1973.
</P>
<P>
According to historical data, out of the ten hottest months of
August, five coincided with the occurrence of El Nino phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
The El Nino episode which has brought disruption to the global
weather since early last year has weakened significantly. It is
expected that the weather in Hong Kong will return gradually to
near normal conditions, according to local weathermen. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
