<HEADLINE> Water Levels Recede at Yangtze, Songhua Rivers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- As the water level of the
middle and lower reaches of the Yangtze River continue to recede,
and navigation has resumed in river sections to the east of Hankou
of Wuhan, capital of Hubei Province.
</P>
<P>
According to a release of the State Flood Control and Drought
Relief Headquarters, the water levels at major Hydrometric
Stations on the Yangtze, and the Dongting and Poyang lakes
continued to drop today, though many are still higher than the
warning mark.
</P>
<P>
However, the water level at Nanjing, capital of Jiangsu
Province, rose to 9.6 meters, owing to the impact of the changing
astronomical tidal conditions, the Headquarters said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile in the northeast, the water level of the Songhua
River also continued to subside.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the Headquarters still calls for continued
anti-flood vigilance so as to guard against any possible hazard
during water-subsiding period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
