<HEADLINE> Iranian Vice President, Culture Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Two key figures within Iran's
moderate government were assaulted Friday by "groups of
unidentified people", the official IRNA news agency reported
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Vice President for Development and Social Affairs Abdollah
Nouri and Minister of Culture and Islamic Guidance Ataollah
Mohajerani were attacked while attending a funeral ceremony for
700 Iranian soldiers fallen in the 1980-88 Iran-Iraq war, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The attackers chanted slogans against Nouri, the former
Interior Minister, who was impeached by the hardline Majlis
(Parliament) in June, and assaulted him and his bodyguards.
</P>
<P>
Nouri was taken to a safe place and then carried away in an
ambulance about 20 minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, another group of people attacked Mohajerani while
he was talking to people attending the funeral.
</P>
<P>
Mohajerani's bodyguards were also attacked, but they did not hit
back, the report said. And several people who tried to intervene
were also beaten up by the attackers.
</P>
<P>
Mohajerani decided to stay on at first, but he was taken by
security officials to a nearby building and driven away.
</P>
<P>
After the incident, Nouri told the IRNA that he had no
complaints against any particular individuals or groups.
</P>
<P>
He also extended his apology to those who were harmed in
defending him.
</P>
<P>
However, Mohajerani refused to answer a question put by the
IRNA on whom may be behind the incident.
</P>
<P>
Despite the assaults, both Nouri and Mohajerani were in good
condition Friday night, the IRNA said.
</P>
<P>
Security authorities are investigating the incident to try to
find out who were behind the attacks, it added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
