<HEADLINE> U.S. Company Wins Two Contracts in Asia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 4 (Xinhua) -- Lucent Technologies Inc., a
U.S. company designs and builds communications and data network
systems, announced Friday that it had won two contracts in Asia,
according to reports from the company.
</P>
<P>
One contract is with China Unicom, China's second largest telephone
network provider, which purchased equipment worth 25 million dollars
from Lucent, the company said.
</P>
<P>
The multi-service contract with China Unicom is aiming at
establishing long distance telephone service in 23 Chinese cities,
Lucent said, adding the project is expected to begin operation in
March, 1999.
</P>
<P>
The other contract is to invest 17 million U.S. dollar in Brunei to
provide Jabatan Telekom Brunei with advanced telecommunications
technology, Lucent said.
</P>
<P>
The contract with Jabatan Telekom Brunei, the country's only
provider of fixed line telephone services, is expected to be completed
by October 1999.  
</P>
