<HEADLINE> Nunn Beats Thomas in Decision in Cruiserweight Fight </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 4 (Xinhua) -- World champion Michael
Nunn beat Glenn Thomas with a unanimous decision in a 10-round
cruiserweight all-American fight Friday night in Miami, the
United States.
</P>
<P>
Nunn, who had held the IBF middleweight and WBA super
-middleweight titles, dominated the fight most of time, but his
punches had little effect on Thomas (26-5), who spent most of the
bout against the ropes.
</P>
<P>
Two judges scored the bout 99-91 for Nunn, while the third had
him winning 100-90. Nunn improved his record to 53-4.
</P>
<P>
In a super-lightweight bout, Diobelys Hurtado stopped Darryl
Tyson, also from the United States, in the fifth round.
Hurtado,ranked sixth by the WBC, floored Tyson (47-11-1) three
times in the final round. The 37-year-old Tyson, in his first
bout since 1996,disputed the second and third knockdowns,
claiming he slipped and was pushed behind the head.
</P>
<P>
But referee Jorge Alonso stopped the bout at 2:30 of the
round.Hurtado, a former member of the Cuban national team, hopes
the victory earns him a WBC super-lightweight title shot. 
</P>
</TEXT>
