stones with a few booths from abroad display goods at the
exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Sri Lanka was referred to as an "island of gem", and historical
evidence showed the gems were an important product of trade during
early times.
</P>
<P>
Many of the largest sapphires in museum collections around the
world were discovered from the gravel of Sri Lanka. With the
discovery of the 850 carats Blue Sapphire last month, Sri Lanka is
still the number one producer of good blue sapphires, said A.
Ellawala, chairman of the National Gem and Jewelry Authority.
</P>
<P>
The export earnings of gems in the country last year were 207.6
million U.S. dollars. 
