<HEADLINE> Central America, Caribbean Barred From Rio Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 4 (Xinhua) -- The Central American and
Caribbean countries will not be admitted into the Group of Rio
(GR) because of opposition from Peru, Paraguay, Brazil and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
The opposition of the most prominent members of this regional
organization to the inclusion of Central America and the Caribbean
is based on the fact that the Group of Rio is only a mechanism of
consultation and discussion.
</P>
<P>
One of the concerns of the South American countries is that the
inclusion of more nations in the group could cause the breaking-up
of the Organization of American States (OAS), which is said by
some of its member countries to be passive in solving the problems
of the hemisphere, and totally dependent on the United States.
</P>
<P>
Peruvian President Alberto Fujimori said the addition of new
members could make it lose the essence of representativeness and
coordination with which it was created.
</P>
<P>
"This mechanism of consultation must not become a Latin America
and the Caribbean summit, because there are already mechanisms for
that," he said.
</P>
<P>
Also, the aim of the Group of Rio was not to have "a small
forum" to analyze current problems, said Fujimori. 
</P>
</TEXT>
