<HEADLINE> Thai Foreign Ministry Help Lower Unemployment Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 5 (Xinhua) -- Thai Foreign Ministry will
contribute its part in helping alleviate the country's mounting
unemployment rate by using a radio network to broadcast job
information, the Bangkok Post reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
From September 15, the ministry will use a radio network of the
Interior Ministry to broadcast information that ordinary people
want to know -- jobs overseas, ways of preventing cheating by
illegal brokers, as well as where people can get jobs.
</P>
<P>
Initially, the Interior Ministry's radio network would be
broadcast to 850 districts and subdistricts across the country.
</P>
<P>
Two months later, the broadcast would reach all 60,000 villages
nationwide, the newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The projects is also a bid to help people, who were laid off
work as a result of the recession, to seek the right channel to
find jobs abroad and discourage opportunities to cheat them.
</P>
<P>
The project would emphasis issues close to the grassroots which
would be broadcast in simple language twice a day. 
