government was contacting Angola's government, its National Union
for the Total Independence of Angola (UNITA) and the People's
Movement for the Liberation of Angola. He asked the United Nations
to take action to prevent the situation in Angola from worsening.
</P>
<P>
Also under discussion were the Bosnian issue, NATO's eastern
expansion and the next NATO summit, Gama said.
</P>
<P>
Solana was in Portugal to attend a NATO seminar on the
challenge human kind would face next century at sea. 
