<HEADLINE> Yunnan Pledges To Accelerate Road Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- The inland Yunnan Province in
southwest China has decided to increase its investment in road
construction by 58 percent, the English-language newspaper China
Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The province, where more than 20 ethnic groups live, will see
an input of eight billion yuan (971 million US dollars) into the
construction of highways by the end of this year, compared with
the 5.1 billion yuan planned in the government's initial budget.
</P>
<P>
This year's road investment matches the total amount invested
by the State between 1985 and 1995, the periods corresponding to
China's seventh and eighth five year plan periods.
</P>
<P>
Experts estimate that the enlarged investment in traffic
infrastructure can contribute by 0.9 percent to the economic
growth of the province this year.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government has also made efforts to attract
foreign investment and has sold management rights for some of the
highways to foreign companies. The construction of new highways is
also expected to involve more foreign investments. 
</P>
