<HEADLINE> China Has Approved Over 314,000 Foreign-Funded Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The newspaper, sponsored by the State Statistics Bureau, noted
that these projects have a combined contractual foreign investment
of 545.366 billion U.S. dollars, of which 242.321 billion
U.S. dollars have already been invested.
</P>
<P>
The last five years have witnessed the fastest growth of
foreign investment in China, and foreign investment is playing an
ever more vital role in the growth of the Chinese economy, the
article said.
</P>
<P>
"Since 1993, China has for five consecutive years remained the
second largest recipient of foreign funds, after the United
States," the paper said.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investment accounted for 14.79 percent of China's total
investment on fixed assets expansion at the end of last year,
while the ratio was a mere 4.2 percent in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded firms now employ 18 million local people, about
10 percent of the country's non-farming population.
</P>
<P>
The foreign investment now covers almost all fields of the
Chinese economy, with infrastructure, energy, raw materials,
communications and high-tech projects taking a more prominent
position over the years.
</P>
<P>
Currently, more than 200 of the world's top 500 firms have
invested in China, a majority of these are involved in the
machinery, electronics and infrastructural sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
