<HEADLINE> Martial Arts to be Performed at Tian'anmen Square </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 5 (Xinhua) -- As many as 10,000 people are
expected to perform Taijiquan, a kind of ancient Chinese martial
arts, at Tian'anmen Square in mid October, the "Beijing Daily" has
reported.
</P>
<P>
Taijiquan is a system of physical exercise that emphasizes
balance, coordination and effortless movements. It is designed for
attaining bodily or mental control and well-being as well as an
art of self-defense.
</P>
<P>
Participants will include Taiji fans from the central Party and
government departments, People's Liberation Army headquarters,
institutions of higher learning, as well as some members of the
foreign Taijiquan organizations who will have come here especially
for the event. And the event will be televised alive worldwide to
mark the 40th anniversary of the founding of the Chinese
Association of Martial Arts.  
</P>
